column12: Method used for calculating power allowance and wireless transmitting/ receiving unit
column13: Disclosed are a method used for calculating power allowance and a wireless transmitting/ receiving unit. The method comprises: determining a carrier wave which has no PUSCH transmission in subframe i from a plurality of aggregate carrier waves; and calculating the power allowance according to the formula: PH(k,i)=PCMAX_carrier (k)-PPUSCH_REF(k,i), wherein PH (k,i) is the power allowance used for the carrier wave, k is the carrier wave, and PPUSCH_REF(k,i) is the emission power determined according to reference authorization distribution.
column15: ZHANG GUODONG;;BALA ERDEM;;PIETRASKI PHILIP J;;SHIN SUNG-HYUK;;PAN KYLE JUNG-LIN;;LEVY JOSEPH S;;WANG JIN;;WANG PETER S;;STERN-BERKOWITZ JANET A;;HAIM JOHN W

column12: Uplink power headroom reporting for carrier aggregation
column13: A method for reporting power headroom is disclosed. Power headroom may be reported across all carriers (wideband), for a specific carrier, or for a carrier group. The formula used to calculate the power headroom depends on whether the carrier (or a carrier in the carrier group) has a valid uplink grant. If the carrier or carrier group does not have a valid uplink grant, the power headroom may be calculated based on a reference grant. The power headroom is calculated by a wireless transmit/receive unit and is reported to an eNodeB.

column12: UPLINK POWER HEADROOM REPORTING FOR CARRIER AGGREGATION
column13: A method for reporting power headroom is disclosed. Power headroom may be reported across all carriers (wideband), for a specific carrier, or for a carrier group. The formula used to calculate the power headroom depends on whether the carrier (or a carrier in the carrier group) has a valid uplink grant. If the carrier or carrier group does not have a valid uplink grant, the power headroom may be calculated based on a reference grant. The power headroom is calculated by a wireless transmit/receive unit and is reported to an eNodeB.

column13: 파워 헤드룸을 보고하는 방법이 개시된다. 파워 헤드룸은 모든 캐리어들에 걸쳐(광대역), 또는 특정 캐리어에 대해, 또는 캐리어 그룹에 대해 보고될 수 있다. 파워 헤드룸을 계산하는데 사용되는 공식은 캐리어(또는 캐리어 그룹 내의 캐리어)가 유효한 업링크 그랜트를 갖는지 여부에 의존한다. 만약 캐리어 또는 캐리어 그룹이 유효한 업링크 그랜트를 갖지 않는다면, 파워 헤드룸은 레퍼런스 그랜트에 근거하여 계산될 수 있다. 파워 헤드룸은 무선 송수신 유닛에 의해 계산되고, eNodeB에 보고된다.

column12: Vegetable seed drying and storing device for vegetable breeding
column13: The invention relates to the field of grain storage, in particular to a vegetable seed drying and storing device for vegetable breeding. The vegetable seed drying and storing device comprises a motor, an output shaft is mounted on one side of the motor, first bearings are mounted on two sides of the middle of the output shaft, the first bearings are connected through a gas circulation cylinder, an electric heating net and an air supply device which are vertically arranged are mounted in the gas circulation cylinder, an upper cover plate and a lower cover plate are mounted at the two ends of the gas circulation cylinder, an arc-shaped cylinder is mounted on the outer sides of the upper cover plate and the lower cover plate, and two corresponding holes in the other side of the arc-shaped cylinder are connected through a drying device. Through the arrangement of the output shaft, the gas circulation cylinder, the upper cover plate, the lower cover plate, the arc-shaped cylinder, the drying device, a synchronous freezing transfer device, the air supply device and a differential mechanism, when the device dries and stores vegetable seeds, the vegetable seeds are uniformly separated in small areas, so that the defects that the drying efficiency is low and the drying effect is poor when the vegetable seeds are collectively stacked for drying and storage are overcome, and storage and further use of the vegetable seeds are facilitated.

column12: Heating equipment for greenhouse seedling raising
column13: The utility model discloses heating equipment for greenhouse seedling raising, which comprises a support frame, the top of the support frame is movably connected with a body, the rear side of the top of the support frame is fixedly connected with a connecting plate, and the top of the support frame is provided with a movable groove. Through cooperative use of the body, the connecting plate, the movable groove, the positioning plate, the clamping groove, the penetrating hole, the containing groove, the through hole, the pull rod, the squeezing plate, the fixing device and the squeezing device, when the positioning plate drives the limiting plate to break away from the limiting groove, the body is pulled forwards to drive the limiting rod to break away from the limiting hole in the front side of the connecting plate, and convenient disassembly of the body is completed; the heating equipment for greenhouse seedling raising solves the problems that existing heating equipment for greenhouse seedling raising is fixed through bolts, when the heating equipment breaks down and needs to be disassembled, time and labor are wasted when the bolts are twisted, and the bolts are prone to slipping, and the heating equipment for greenhouse seedling raising has the advantage of being convenient to disassemble and is worthy of popularization.

column12: Seeding disc for non-toxic breeding of vegetables
column13: The utility model discloses a vegetable non-toxic breeding seeding tray, which comprises a body, the front side of the body is fixedly connected with a first supporting plate, the top of the first supporting plate is fixedly connected with two storage boxes, the front side of the first supporting plate is fixedly connected with two second supporting plates, and the second supporting plates are fixedly connected with the top of the first supporting plate. A supporting rod is fixedly connected to the bottom of the second supporting plate, a first shell is fixedly connected to the bottom of the supporting rod, a second shell is movably connected to the right side of the first shell, a seeding disc is fixedly connected to the interior of the first shell, and a plurality of through holes are formed in the surface of the seeding disc. Through cooperative use of the body, the first supporting plate, the storage box, the second supporting plate, the supporting rod, the first shell, the second shell, the seeding disc, a through hole, a limiting mechanism, a rotating mechanism, a sliding sleeve, a rotating block, a sliding block and a sliding groove, the effects and advantages that time and labor are saved during mounting and dismounting, and internal maintenance is facilitated are achieved.

column12: Threshing equipment for vegetable seed treatment
column13: The invention relates to the technical field of vegetable planting, and discloses threshing equipment for vegetable seed treatment. The threshing equipment comprises a working table, a supporting component is arranged at the bottom of the working table, a beating assembly is arranged on the working table, a conveying assembly is arranged on one side of the working table, a top plate is arranged at a position, matched with the beating assembly, of one side of the working table, a second yield groove is formed in the top plate, a rotating shaft is arranged on the second yield groove and rotationally connected with one side of a first rotating support, a first clamping plate is arranged at the end, away from the rotating shaft, of the first rotating support, a hinge joint is arranged between the first clamping plate and the first rotating support, and a reciprocating driving assembly is arranged at the end, close to the rotating shaft, of the first rotating support. According to the threshing equipment for vegetable seed treatment, the first clamping plate and a second clamping plate are arranged to drive vegetables to move relative to a beating rod, the beating threshing effect is achieved, therefore, the machine threshing effect is achieved, and the production efficiency is improved.

column12: Irrigation equipment for vegetable breeding
column13: The irrigation equipment for vegetable breeding comprises a machine body, the rear side of the machine body is communicated with a water inlet, the inner wall of the water inlet is movably connected with a conveying pipe, the surface of the conveying pipe is fixedly connected with a matching block, and the two sides of the front side of the matching block are fixedly connected with fixing blocks. A clamping groove used in cooperation with the fixing block is formed in the rear side of the water inlet. The machine body, the water inlet, the transmission pipe, the matching block, the fixed block, the clamping groove, the fixed groove, a limiting mechanism, a movable block, a limiting rod, a traction rod, a transmission rod, an adjusting mechanism, a pull ring, an adjusting rod, a transmission block, a tension spring, a limiting groove, a limiting hole, an adjusting hole, a transmission groove, a sliding block, a sliding groove and a sealing ring are used in cooperation. The problems that connection between a water inlet and a conveying pipe in an existing irrigation device is too tedious, and leakage occurs due to the fact that the connection position is not tight enough due to improper operation of a user are solved.

column12: Seedling conveying device for vegetable seedling raising
column13: The invention discloses a seedling conveying device for vegetable seedling, and relates to the field of conveying and transportation, the seedling conveying device comprises a base, a first placing basket is mounted on the upper side of the base, and spur racks are slidably mounted on the upper sides of the base on two opposite sides of the first placing basket; rotating wheels are installed at the two ends of the upper side of the spur rack in a matched mode correspondingly, rotating rods are fixedly connected to the rotating wheels, rotating grooves are formed in the rotating rods, rotating columns are installed in the rotating grooves in a matched mode, air cylinders are fixedly arranged on the upper side of the base, air rods are installed on the air cylinders in a matched mode, and the other ends of the air rods are connected with the spur rack; damping rods are symmetrically connected to the upper ends of the sliding blocks, a pair of moving grooves are symmetrically formed in the two ends of the side, right opposite to and adjacent to the damping plate, of the base, moving blocks are cooperatively installed in the moving grooves, moving springs are installed in the moving grooves, and the other ends of the moving springs are connected to the moving blocks. The seedling conveying device is advantages in that reasonable design is realized; the seedling raising pot can be clamped and fixed and is convenient to store, and the stability in the transportation process is improved.

column12: Temperature control equipment for vegetable breeding
column13: The utility model discloses temperature control equipment for vegetable breeding, which comprises an equipment body, a protective device is arranged on the front side of the equipment body, positioning holes are formed in the top and the bottom of the rear side of the protective device, positioning blocks are arranged in inner cavities of the positioning holes, movable grooves are formed in inner cavities of the positioning blocks, and the movable grooves are communicated with the protective device. An adjusting mechanism is arranged in an inner cavity of the movable groove, a first through hole used in cooperation with the adjusting mechanism is formed in the front side of the movable groove, and a fixing mechanism used in cooperation with the adjusting mechanism is arranged at the top of the movable groove at the top. Through cooperative use of the equipment body, the protection device, a positioning hole, a positioning block, a movable groove, an adjusting mechanism, a first through hole, a fixing mechanism, a limiting groove and a third through hole, the problems that the protection device of existing temperature control equipment is inconvenient to install, tools are needed in the installation process of the existing temperature control equipment, installation is strenuous, and the installation cost is high are solved. And the working efficiency is reduced.

column12: Ventilation device for vegetable breeding
column13: The utility model discloses a vegetable breeding ventilation device which comprises a ventilator, a movable groove is formed in the surface of the ventilator, a transmission mechanism is arranged in the movable groove, and a clamping mechanism is arranged in the movable groove. The ventilator, the movable groove, the transmission mechanism, the first abutting plate, the second abutting plate, a first abutting block, a first spring, a clamping mechanism, a second abutting block, a connecting plate, a second spring, a sliding plate, a dust filter screen, a first sliding block, a second sliding block, a first sliding groove, a second sliding groove, a clamping groove, a button, a clamping block and a handle are used in cooperation. The novel ventilator has the advantages that the dust filter screen is convenient to disassemble and assemble, and the problems that dust in air can be filtered on the surface of the dust filter screen when the air is replaced by an existing ventilator, the surface of the dust filter screen needs to be timely cleaned by a user due to long-time ventilation, and the dust filter screen is inconvenient to disassemble and assemble by the user due to the fact that the dust filter screen is relatively complex to fix are solved.

column12: Tray for non-toxic breeding of vegetables
column13: The utility model discloses a vegetable non-toxic breeding tray which comprises a water storage basin, a tray body is arranged in the water storage basin, clamping blocks are fixedly connected to the two sides of the top of the water storage basin, limiting grooves are formed in the front side and the rear side of each clamping block, and fixing blocks are fixedly connected to the two sides of the tray body. The water storage basin, the tray body, the clamping block, the limiting groove, the fixing block, the clamping groove, the fixing groove, the limiting mechanism, the rotating rod, the connecting rod, the limiting rod, the transmission block, the adjusting mechanism, the sliding rod, the sliding sleeve, the adjusting rod, the tension spring, the traction rod, the transmission rod, the adjusting block, the transmission groove, the adjusting hole and the limiting hole are used in cooperation; the problems that when an existing tray is matched with a water storage basin at the bottom, the tray does not have a limiting function and is prone to shaking, and therefore a user mistakenly touches the water storage basin, and seeds in the tray fall off due to the too large shaking amplitude are solved.

column12: DEVICE AND METHOD OF CONTROLLING UPLINK POWER FOR WIRELESS TRANSMIT/RECEIVE UNIT USING MULTIPLE CARRIERS
column13: FIELD: radio engineering, communication.SUBSTANCE: invention relates to wireless communication. The invention discloses a method and a device for determining uplink power on a WTRU. The WTRU operates in an aggregated carrier system. The WTRU is configured to receive a plurality of uplink power parameters allocated to one of a plurality of uplink carriers and to receive a transmitted power control command allocated to one of the plurality of uplink carriers. The WTRU is configured to determine path losses for one of the plurality of uplink carriers and to determine transmitted power for one of the plurality of uplink carriers based on the plurality of power parameters, the transmitted power control command and path losses.EFFECT: enabling a wireless transmit/receive unit (WTRU) to perform complex operations for proper UL transmission power control.16 cl, 4 tbl, 10 dwg

column12: APARATO Y METODO PARA CONTROL ASCENDENTE DE POTENCIA PARA UNA UNIDAD INALAMBRICA TRANSMISORA/RECEPTORA UTILIZANDO MULTIPLES PORTADORES.
column13: Un método y aparato para determinar la potencia del enlace ascendente en una unidad de transmision/recepcion inalámbrica (WTRU). La WTRU funciona en un sistema de portadora agregada. La WTRU está configurada para recibir una pluralidad de parámetros de potencia del enlace ascendente indizados hacia una portadora de una pluralidad de portadoras del enlace ascendente y para recibir un comando de control de potencia de transmision indizado hacia una portadora de una pluralidad de portadoras del enlace ascendente. La WTRU está configurada para determinar una pérdida de trayectoria de une portadora de una pluralidad de portadoras del enlace ascendente y determinar una potencia de trasmision para la portadora de la pluralidad de portadoras del enlace ascendente basándose en la pluralidad de parámetros de potencia, el comando de control de potencia de transmision y la perdida de trayectoria.

column12: Apparatus and method for uplink power control for a wireless transmitter/receiver unit utilizing multiple carriers
column13: A method and apparatus for determining uplink power in a wireless transmit receive unit (WTRU). The WTRU operates in a carrier aggregated system. The WTRU is configured to receive a plurality of uplink power parameters indexed to one of a plurality of uplink carriers and receive a transmit power control command indexed to the one of the plurality of uplink carriers. The WTRU is configured to determine a pathloss of the one of the plurality of uplink carriers and determine a transmit power for the one of the plurality of uplink carriers based on the plurality of power parameters, the transmit power control command, and the pathloss.

column12: Apparatus and method for uplink power control for a wireless transmitter/receiver unit utilizing multiple carriers
column13: A method and apparatus for determining uplink power in a wireless transmit receive unit (WTRU). The WTRU operates in a carrier aggregated system. The WTRU is configured to receive a plurality of uplink power parameters indexed to one of a plurality of uplink carriers and receive a transmit power control command indexed to the one of the plurality of uplink carriers. The WTRU is configured to determine a pathloss of the one of the plurality of uplink carriers and determine a transmit power for the one of the plurality of uplink carriers based on the plurality of power parameters, the transmit power control command, and the pathloss.

column12: Method for performing uplink power control in WTRU, and WTRU
column13: The invention disclose a method for performing uplink power control in a wireless transmit receive unit (WTRU) and a WTRU. The WTRU is at least partially configured to transmit a first uplink channel and a second uplink channel at the same time on one or more uplink carriers. The method includes the steps: determining the power grade of the first uplink channel; comparing the power grade of the first uplink channle with the threshold corresponding to at least oen uplink carrier so as to determine the power difference; determining the value of the power grade of the second uplink channle, corresponding to the at least one uplink carrier; and setting the power grade of the second uplink channle as the power difference or the lower one among the determined values.

column12: Method for uplink power control on a wireless transmitter/receiver unit (WTRU) and WTRU
column13: The invention discloses a method for performing uplink power control on a WTRU and the WTRU. The method comprises the following steps: determining that the WTRU is configured to simultaneously transmit a physical uplink shared channel (PUSCH) and a physical uplink control channel (PUCCH) in a sub-frame on one carrier of one or more aggregated carriers; determining the maximum transmission power; determining a PUSCH transmission power used for PUSCH transmission in the sub-frame of the carrier; determining PUCCH transmission power used for PUCCH transmission in the subframe of the carrier wave;determining the power margin of the carrier by using the maximum transmission power, the PUSCH transmission power and the PUCCH transmission power; and transmitting a power headroom report includingthe power headroom.

column12: APPARATUS AND METHOD FOR UPLINK POWER CONTROL FOR WIRELESS TRANSMITTER/RECEIVER UNIT UTILIZING MULTIPLE CARRIERS
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a method and an apparatus for determining uplink power in a wireless transmit receive unit (WTRU).SOLUTION: A WTRU operates in a carrier aggregated system. The WTRU is configured to receive a plurality of uplink power parameters indexed to one of a plurality of uplink carriers and receive a transmit power control command indexed to the one of the plurality of uplink carriers. The WTRU is configured to determine a path loss of one of the plurality of uplink carriers and determine transmit power for the one of the plurality of uplink carriers on the basis of the plurality of power parameters, the transmit power control command, and the path loss.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 8

column12: Method for performing uplink control on wireless transmitter/receiver unit (WTRU), and WTRU
column13: A method for performing uplink control on a wireless transmitter/receiver unit (WTRU) and theWTRU are disclosed. The WTRU is at least partically configured to simultaneously transmit a first uplink channel and a second uplink channel in one or more uplink carriers. The method comprises determining a power stage of the first uplink channel, comparing the power stage of the first uplink channel and a threshold corresponding t o at least one uplink carrier to determine a power difference, determining a value of the power stage of the second uplink channel corresponding to at least one uplink carrier, and setting the power stage of the second uplink chanel to be the power difference or one lower value of the determined values.

column12: Aparatos para terapia de herida por presión negativa
column13: Un adaptador de succión adecuado para tratar un lugar de herida con presión negativa, que comprende: un aplicador (1520, 5520) que tiene una superficie superior y una superficie inferior; y un puente (1502, 5502) que tiene un extremo proximal y un extremo distal, el extremo distal del puente conectado a la superficie superior del aplicador, el puente (1502, 5502) comprende: un paso de fluido superior (1512, 5512) conectado a una fuga de aire (1524, 5524); y caracterizado por un paso de fluido inferior (1516, 5516) en comunicación de fluidos con una fuente de presión negativa, el paso de fluido inferior (1516, 5516) comprende un material de punto 3D.

column12: Apparatuses and methods for negative pressure wound therapy
column13: Disclosed herein are several embodiments of a negative pressure appliance and methods of using the same in the treatment of wounds. Some embodiments are directed to improved fluidic connectors or suction adapters for connecting to a wound site, for example using softer, kink-free conformable suction adapters.

column12: APPARATUS AND METHOD FOR NEGATIVE PRESSURE-CLOSED TREATMENT
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a negative pressure generating apparatus and methods for using the same in the treatment of wounds.SOLUTION: A wound site 5530 is cleaned and prepared in a suitable fashion, and a drape 5531 of the system 5501 is placed into the wound site. An aperture 5535 through the drape to the wound site is created and then the applicator portion 5520 is situated over the aperture. After the backing layer 5529 is removed from the adhesive layer on the underside of the applicator portion, the applicator is sealed to the drape, and the backing layer is also removed from the applicator portion. A fluidic conduit such as a tube 5540 may then be connected to the connector 5504. The tube may also be connected to the connector before the applicator is applied to the wound site. The fluidic conduit is connected to a source of negative pressure 5534, preferably with a container suitable for containing wound exudate interposed therebetween. The negative pressure may then be applied to the wound site until the wound site progresses to a desired level of healing.

column12: COMPOUNDS AND METHODS FOR TARGETING LEUKEMIC STEM CELLS
